7 Un’aura dolce, sanza mutamento 8 avere in sé, mi feria per la fronte 9 non di più colpo che soave vento;
10 per cui le fronde, tremolando, pronte 11 tutte quante piegavano a la parte 12 u’ la prim’ ombra gitta il santo monte;
13 non però dal loro esser dritto sparte 14 tanto, che li augelletti per le cime 15 lasciasser d’operare ogne lor arte;
16 ma con piena letizia l’ore prime, 17 cantando, ricevieno intra le foglie, 18 che tenevan bordone a le sue rime,
19 tal qual di ramo in ramo si raccoglie 20 per la pineta in su ’l lito di Chiassi, 21 quand’ Ëolo scilocco fuor discioglie.

query.result:
**English:**
7 A gentle breeze, without any change 8 in itself, struck my forehead 9 no more forcefully than a soft wind;
10 because of which the leaves, trembling, quickly 11 all leaned toward the side 12 where the holy mountain cast its first shadow;
13 yet they were not separated from their upright position 14 so much that the little birds in the treetops 15 stopped practicing all their arts;
16 but with full joy they welcomed the early hours, 17 singing, among the leaves, 18 which provided a drone to their melodies,
19 just as it gathers from branch to branch 20 through the pine forest on the shore of Chiassi, 21 when Aeolus releases the southeast wind.
**Sanskrit:**
