query.result:
**English:**
103 Now, why does the air revolve completely 104 with the first revolution, 105 if its circle is not broken by some obstacle,
106 at this height where it is completely dissolved 107 in the living air, such motion strikes it, 108 and makes the forest resound because it is dense;
109 and the struck plant has so much power 110 that it impregnates the air with its virtue, 111 and that air, whirling, then scatters it around;
112 and the other earth, according to its worthiness 113 in itself and because of its sky, conceives and produces 114 different kinds of wood with different virtues.
